    <thetext>Section 8.1.5 introduces the term &apos;positive Infinity&apos;, and says that it&apos;s also referred to &quot;for expository purposes&quot; by the symbol &apos;+ï‚¥&apos;. [That character may not render properly, but you know what I mean.]

There are two places in the spec that denote this value with other terms:

    In 9.1.8.1 &quot;ToString Applied to the Number Type&quot;,
    step 4 says:
        If m is infinity, return the String &quot;Infinity&quot;.

    In 15.4.6.2.2 &quot;ArrayIterator.prototype.next( )&quot;,
    step 11.a says:
        Set the value of the [[ArrayIteratorNextIndex]] internal data property
        of O to +Infinity.

In each case, the improper term (&quot;infinity&quot; or &quot;+Infinity&quot;) should be changed to either &quot;positive Infinity&quot; or the symbol. For consistency with all other pseudo-code in the spec, use the symbol.</thetext>
